main event: An oval object, the size of a pan, appeared to be floating in Pensacola, Florida on May 25, 1959.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 1 minute when first sighted and up to 5 minutes when last seen., The investigation officer considered it as an anti-collision light., The sighting was categorized as a ground-visual observation., The object was described as being red and flashing., There were five high-quality photos taken, although none are present in the report.
witness description: A/3C Tur Operator with reliability unknown
